comments: Wood (DAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard Collins (ATL).
Bullock (DAL) establishes himself in Hunter's (ATL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Collins (ATL) and Finney-Smith (DAL) come together during the rebound and incidental  leg to leg contact occurs.
Hunter (ATL) makes contact with the ball as simultaneous marginal contact occurs with Dinwiddie's (DAL) left arm during the rebound.
Bullock (DAL) maintains his left pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Collins (ATL) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Bullock's (DAL) driving shot attempt.
Capela (ATL) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Young (ATL) maintains his right hand on the side of the ball during his dribble.
Wood (DAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard Young (ATL).

Hunter (ATL) contests the shot attempt at the rim and marginal contact occurs with Finney-Smith's (DAL) head after release. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Bullock (DAL) attempts to take a foul on Young (ATL) but makes marginal contact.
Bullock (DAL) commits a take foul on Young (ATL). The contact occurs prior to Young's gather and upward shooting motion.
Bullock (DAL) commits a take foul on Young (ATL).
Collins (ATL) and Wood (DAL) engage in marginal hand to hand contact during the rebound.
Collins (ATL) and Wood (DAL) briefly engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Wood (DAL) makes incidental hand on ball contact as he dislodges the ball away from Collins (ATL) during the rebound.
Wood (DAL) commits a take foul on Young (ATL).
